1
00:00:00,049 --> 00:02:00,049
(Watch on www.kisskh.club Support Admin)

2
00:02:56,273 --> 00:02:57,707
Van's right.

3
00:02:57,732 --> 00:02:58,900
It's my fault.

4
00:03:01,038 --> 00:03:02,331
I was being selfish.

5
00:03:03,091 --> 00:03:05,427
I didn't think about
how you would feel.

6
00:03:05,849 --> 00:03:07,226
I'm really sorry, guys.

7
00:03:10,912 --> 00:03:12,125
Wait

8
00:03:12,364 --> 00:03:13,824
was Dave with you?

9
00:03:14,327 --> 00:03:15,828
He hasn't come back
from his classes.

10
00:03:16,165 --> 00:03:17,458
Let's look for him!

11
00:03:17,645 --> 00:03:19,146
Dave, where have you been?

12
00:03:20,062 --> 00:03:21,946
I needed fresh air after class.

13
00:03:22,090 --> 00:03:23,914
On the verge of Bloody Night?

14
00:03:25,802 --> 00:03:28,805
Do I need to be a demon like them?

15
00:03:32,642 --> 00:03:35,520
Do I need to be more
savage than them?

16
00:03:37,439 --> 00:03:40,150
I am the Supreme Student Secretary.

17
00:03:41,026 --> 00:03:43,111
I have the right to object

18
00:03:43,862 --> 00:03:45,113
to your decisions.

19
00:03:48,843 --> 00:03:51,511
Let us talk about the big event

20
00:03:51,536 --> 00:03:54,247
that's going to happen in this school.

21
00:03:54,372 --> 00:03:56,374
And we will call it.

22
00:03:56,541 --> 00:03:58,376
Bloody Week.

23
00:03:58,460 --> 00:04:02,714
Where killing is legal in
a span of a week.

24
00:04:03,757 --> 00:04:05,675
At any time.

25
00:04:05,926 --> 00:04:08,178
We know that you know HU's secrets.

26
00:04:08,386 --> 00:04:12,098
I will do everything in my power so
all of you can leave this hellhole.

27
00:04:15,936 --> 00:04:17,479
What happened to you?

28
00:04:21,012 --> 00:04:24,511
I was one of their test subjects for
the serum that they're making.

29
00:04:26,031 --> 00:04:28,450
This is an order from the SSG President

30
00:04:29,702 --> 00:04:31,037
if I say something

31
00:04:31,868 --> 00:04:32,953
you answer quickly.

32
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:35,120
Got it?

33
00:04:38,849 --> 00:04:39,849
You know

34
00:04:41,322 --> 00:04:43,283
you just might be my Achilles' heel.

35
00:04:44,381 --> 00:04:45,381
Ms. Shion.

36
00:05:31,187 --> 00:05:33,911
Just tell me where the
laboratory is hidden.

37
00:05:38,518 --> 00:05:39,227
Come with me.

38
00:05:39,227 --> 00:05:40,227
I'll show you.

39
00:05:48,528 --> 00:05:50,030
Where's the laboratory?

40
00:05:51,635 --> 00:05:54,179
Just tell me where
the laboratory is.

41
00:05:54,204 --> 00:05:56,540
The laboratory you're
looking for is...

42
00:05:58,925 --> 00:06:01,558
It's hidden at...

43
00:06:01,583 --> 00:06:03,376
Just tell me where it is please.

44
00:06:03,401 --> 00:06:05,445
It's hidden at...

45
00:07:52,777 --> 00:07:54,363
What are you doing?

46
00:07:54,969 --> 00:07:56,558
What the fuck!

47
00:07:56,883 --> 00:07:58,427
She’s going to die anyway.

48
00:07:59,659 --> 00:08:01,661
I saved her from her suffering.

49
00:08:02,018 --> 00:08:04,729
Why are you doing this
you crazy bitch?

50
00:08:05,757 --> 00:08:07,402
I'm just saving you.

51
00:08:08,379 --> 00:08:09,379
Us.

52
00:08:09,992 --> 00:08:11,953
Stay away from Alvarez.

53
00:08:17,988 --> 00:08:19,179
Chill

54
00:08:21,139 --> 00:08:23,266
hurting me won't do you any good.

55
00:08:45,346 --> 00:08:47,056
I'm just saving you.

56
00:08:47,952 --> 00:08:48,952
Us.

57
00:08:49,290 --> 00:08:51,716
Stay away from Alvarez.

58
00:08:51,836 --> 00:08:52,836
Listen, Zein.

59
00:08:53,630 --> 00:08:55,465
If you accept Ace's offer

60
00:08:56,341 --> 00:08:58,091
you'll be able to find out

61
00:08:58,092 --> 00:09:00,178
where the hidden laboratory is.

62
00:09:01,721 --> 00:09:02,764
Secret lab.

63
00:09:03,606 --> 00:09:05,775
Being the SSG secretary
has its benefits.

64
00:09:06,505 --> 00:09:07,506
You'll know everything.

65
00:09:08,272 --> 00:09:09,982
Learn things no one else can.

66
00:09:11,304 --> 00:09:12,848
Once you take this position

67
00:09:14,984 --> 00:09:16,111
you'll have control

68
00:09:23,284 --> 00:09:24,534
and people will fear you for it.

69
00:09:24,535 --> 00:09:25,286
They're heartless!

70
00:09:25,287 --> 00:09:26,663
Monsters!

71
00:09:27,037 --> 00:09:28,223
You're just like them.

72
00:09:28,248 --> 00:09:29,249
You're a monster too.

73
00:09:29,811 --> 00:09:31,935
We thought you're
the next Samantha

74
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:34,420
but just like her,
you can't change anything.

75
00:09:38,917 --> 00:09:40,786
Why was she able to do something?

76
00:09:41,224 --> 00:09:42,350
I thought...

77
00:09:43,263 --> 00:09:45,306
you're like Samantha.

78
00:09:46,062 --> 00:09:47,062
But you're not.

79
00:09:47,673 --> 00:09:48,826
You're a coward.

80
00:09:48,851 --> 00:09:50,491
Who is this Samantha
they keep mentioning?

81
00:09:51,560 --> 00:09:53,562
Why are they calling
me her name?

82
00:09:54,725 --> 00:09:56,018
Who is she?

83
00:10:01,283 --> 00:10:02,784
Her name is Samantha.

84
00:10:03,626 --> 00:10:05,961
We all thought it would last forever.

85
00:10:06,553 --> 00:10:09,098
But nothing is for sure here in Hell U

86
00:10:09,706 --> 00:10:11,874
except for bloodshed and death.

87
00:10:13,876 --> 00:10:15,684
What's worse is...

88
00:10:17,747 --> 00:10:21,042
the demons became more brutal.

89
00:10:36,858 --> 00:10:38,817
Are you going to help us or not?

90
00:10:38,818 --> 00:10:40,903
Us? There are others?

91
00:10:42,183 --> 00:10:42,964
Wait!

92
00:10:42,989 --> 00:10:44,282
Where are you going?

93
00:10:44,324 --> 00:10:45,718
I still have a lot of questions left.

94
00:10:45,742 --> 00:10:46,993
Where is the lab?

95
00:10:52,749 --> 00:10:54,584
Just tell me where it is please!

96
00:11:05,595 --> 00:11:07,764
It's better to be careful, Zein.

97
00:11:08,598 --> 00:11:11,559
Because our lives are in your hands.

98
00:11:15,229 --> 00:11:18,524
Don't ever cross the line with them.

99
00:11:29,118 --> 00:11:30,827
I've been explaining this multiple times

100
00:11:30,828 --> 00:11:32,329
and you still can't understand?

101
00:11:32,330 --> 00:11:34,373
My throat is hurting
from all these lectures!

102
00:11:34,374 --> 00:11:36,291
How are you this stupid?

103
00:11:36,292 --> 00:11:37,501
Get a grip!

104
00:11:37,502 --> 00:11:39,669
What do you want to happen?

105
00:11:39,670 --> 00:11:41,797
Are you going to be
this stupid forever?

106
00:11:41,798 --> 00:11:42,798
I'm sorry, ma'am.

107
00:11:43,424 --> 00:11:45,543
That's just a piece of cake, idiot!

108
00:11:45,568 --> 00:11:47,110
You never listen to any of it

109
00:11:47,261 --> 00:11:48,929
that's why it doesn't
seep into your brain!

110
00:11:48,930 --> 00:11:49,906
Airhead!

111
00:11:49,931 --> 00:11:52,140
Enough. I told you
to stop it, didn't I?

112
00:11:52,141 --> 00:11:53,266
How dare you!

113
00:11:53,267 --> 00:11:55,560
You stupid girl!

114
00:11:55,561 --> 00:11:57,938
You brain doesn't absorb
anything doesn't it?

115
00:11:57,939 --> 00:11:59,398
I said stop it!

116
00:11:59,399 --> 00:12:00,732
I'm so tired of this!

117
00:12:00,733 --> 00:12:02,401
You're always picking on me.

118
00:12:02,402 --> 00:12:03,819
Embarrassing me.

119
00:12:03,820 --> 00:12:05,780
I have no face to show
because of you.

120
00:12:06,364 --> 00:12:08,866
If I'm stupid

121
00:12:09,534 --> 00:12:11,577
and you're smart?

122
00:12:11,786 --> 00:12:14,137
Prove it to me and answer this question.

123
00:12:14,205 --> 00:12:16,519
When do you think
you're going to die?

124
00:12:49,883 --> 00:12:52,469
I'm aware a lot will
happen this Bloody Week.

125
00:12:53,687 --> 00:12:56,288
But I didn't expect it would be this bad.

126
00:12:57,790 --> 00:12:59,225
The week has barely started

127
00:12:59,250 --> 00:13:02,670
but this is already unbearable to me.

128
00:13:05,076 --> 00:13:07,531
How worse can it get in the incoming days?

129
00:13:07,956 --> 00:13:10,459
What are the horrors in store for us?

130
00:13:18,186 --> 00:13:18,561
Zein!

131
00:13:18,561 --> 00:13:19,561
I'm going to kill you!

132
00:13:39,784 --> 00:13:43,156
There are moments
where I start to lose hope.

133
00:13:43,188 --> 00:13:46,570
that we'll make it out
of Hell University alive.

134
00:13:47,076 --> 00:13:50,329
My friends are my only source of strength

135
00:13:51,010 --> 00:13:52,595
to continue fighting.

136
00:13:53,071 --> 00:13:54,071
Hey...

137
00:13:54,292 --> 00:13:55,836
you're spacing out again.

138
00:14:00,061 --> 00:14:01,896
We're going to get through this.

139
00:14:03,814 --> 00:14:04,982
Where are they?

140
00:14:18,267 --> 00:14:19,560
You know what, Zein

141
00:14:23,709 --> 00:14:25,627
with everything going on.

142
00:14:25,628 --> 00:14:29,048
My fear and nervousness

143
00:14:29,426 --> 00:14:31,261
lessens when we're together.

144
00:14:34,838 --> 00:14:36,089
Just like yesterday

145
00:14:37,181 --> 00:14:38,808
you made us worry

146
00:14:38,833 --> 00:14:41,669
but we trust you.

147
00:14:43,354 --> 00:14:45,147
Didn't we make a promise

148
00:14:45,356 --> 00:14:47,191
that we'll stick together?

149
00:14:52,822 --> 00:14:54,240
I need to go.

150
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:57,031
I thought we'll stick together?

151
00:14:57,733 --> 00:14:58,984
We are sticking together

152
00:15:01,429 --> 00:15:02,638
we'll see each other again.

153
00:15:04,750 --> 00:15:05,960
But I need to do something.

154
00:15:07,268 --> 00:15:10,476
You know as a sexytary.

155
00:15:11,591 --> 00:15:13,976
I like that. Sexytary.

156
00:15:15,970 --> 00:15:18,848
And Van's there.

157
00:15:19,966 --> 00:15:21,175
You won't be alone.

158
00:15:22,059 --> 00:15:23,811
So don't worry too much, okay?

159
00:15:24,919 --> 00:15:25,919
Go on.

160
00:15:26,491 --> 00:15:28,827
Do a good job, Ms. Sexytary.

161
00:15:32,818 --> 00:15:34,171
Come join us, Zein!

162
00:15:34,196 --> 00:15:35,239
Catch this, Zein!

163
00:15:36,735 --> 00:15:37,736
- Bye, Zein.
- Bye.

164
00:15:40,453 --> 00:15:42,038
- She's so busy.
- Hurry!

165
00:15:42,330 --> 00:15:43,330
Here, Dave.

166
00:15:43,414 --> 00:15:44,414
Nice one.

167
00:15:50,086 --> 00:15:51,504
I'm still supposed to be angry at him

168
00:15:51,505 --> 00:15:53,425
after he didn't do anything
to stop Bloody Week.

169
00:15:54,589 --> 00:15:55,589
But I don't know.

170
00:15:56,260 --> 00:15:58,595
I'm still impressed by his
bravery and composure

171
00:15:58,596 --> 00:16:00,097
amidst the chaos.

172
00:16:01,116 --> 00:16:02,116
He's built different.

173
00:16:03,142 --> 00:16:06,680
I still can't believe he
protected me from Madam Violet.

174
00:16:06,911 --> 00:16:08,789
At least he's still fair.

175
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:11,232
Does he think of me as a friend?

176
00:16:11,233 --> 00:16:12,859
Alex Mendoza, Supremo.

177
00:16:19,325 --> 00:16:20,534
X on it, Ms. Shion.

178
00:16:23,907 --> 00:16:24,907
Do it!

179
00:16:25,581 --> 00:16:26,624
But why?

180
00:16:28,131 --> 00:16:29,340
He's still alive.

181
00:16:30,443 --> 00:16:32,904
You're wasting our time here, Ms. Shion.

182
00:16:36,926 --> 00:16:38,219
If you were in my shoes

183
00:16:38,816 --> 00:16:39,900
what would you do?

184
00:16:42,682 --> 00:16:43,849
I would save him.

185
00:16:43,874 --> 00:16:44,874
Okay.

186
00:16:45,184 --> 00:16:47,061
Let's say we help him

187
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:48,729
and he lives.

188
00:16:49,605 --> 00:16:51,357
What do you think will happen next?

189
00:16:52,024 --> 00:16:53,024
That'll be all?

190
00:16:53,049 --> 00:16:54,884
Will his enemies let him stay alive?

191
00:16:59,047 --> 00:17:00,073
But...

192
00:17:00,950 --> 00:17:03,369
Why waste my time with someone
who’s supposed to be dead?

193
00:17:05,121 --> 00:17:08,040
We can't save everyone, Ms. Shion.

194
00:17:10,751 --> 00:17:12,544
You and Matt said the same thing.

195
00:17:12,545 --> 00:17:14,296
I'm going to kill you!

196
00:17:17,675 --> 00:17:18,675
Zein!

197
00:17:18,700 --> 00:17:20,160
Killing is legal now.

198
00:17:20,553 --> 00:17:22,471
You might get hurt from
stepping in their fight!

199
00:17:23,514 --> 00:17:26,350
We can't save everybody Zein!

200
00:17:28,183 --> 00:17:29,768
Matt said the same thing.

201
00:17:56,536 --> 00:17:57,537
Sir Alvarez

202
00:17:58,105 --> 00:17:59,905
you're ten minutes late
for your next subject.

203
00:18:00,087 --> 00:18:01,505
I needed to do something, Supremo.

204
00:18:01,886 --> 00:18:02,970
I'm rushing over there.

205
00:18:07,227 --> 00:18:08,227
Excuse me.

206
00:18:14,573 --> 00:18:16,200
What's your relationship with him?

207
00:18:17,552 --> 00:18:18,552
Nothing.

208
00:18:23,302 --> 00:18:24,303
Supremo.

209
00:18:33,146 --> 00:18:34,811
I've secured the files.

210
00:18:37,955 --> 00:18:40,374
Um... Supremo

211
00:18:41,091 --> 00:18:43,052
is there anything else
you need me to do?

212
00:18:46,096 --> 00:18:47,096
None.

213
00:18:48,808 --> 00:18:49,808
You're good.

214
00:18:50,384 --> 00:18:52,929
Angelica, show me through it.

215
00:18:53,354 --> 00:18:54,354
Okay.

216
00:18:55,812 --> 00:18:57,063
I can review.

217
00:19:00,308 --> 00:19:01,309
You can leave.

218
00:19:03,757 --> 00:19:05,817
But my duty is not done.

219
00:19:05,842 --> 00:19:06,842
Excuse me?

220
00:19:08,811 --> 00:19:10,271
Angelica and I can handle it.

221
00:19:10,881 --> 00:19:11,881
We can take it from here.

222
00:19:12,998 --> 00:19:14,725
Really? Angelica?

223
00:19:15,308 --> 00:19:17,144
Supremo called her by her first name

224
00:19:17,278 --> 00:19:19,272
while he calls me by my surname?

225
00:19:20,363 --> 00:19:21,834
What am I even talking aboout?

226
00:19:24,093 --> 00:19:25,970
Matthew might be looking for you.

227
00:19:28,280 --> 00:19:29,280
Obviously.

228
00:19:38,281 --> 00:19:39,553
They're so annoying!

229
00:19:39,709 --> 00:19:41,123
Who does he think he is?

230
00:19:41,710 --> 00:19:43,303
You have a lot of nerve, Supremo.

231
00:19:47,851 --> 00:19:49,186
This one, solve this.

232
00:20:12,516 --> 00:20:13,516
Try me.

233
00:20:14,052 --> 00:20:15,108
Don't you dare!

234
00:20:17,017 --> 00:20:18,309
Let me go!

235
00:20:18,334 --> 00:20:19,334
Be quiet!

236
00:20:20,607 --> 00:20:21,775
Shut up, stay away.

237
00:20:21,940 --> 00:20:23,652
Get me out of this hell!

238
00:20:23,951 --> 00:20:24,903
Let go off me!

239
00:20:24,904 --> 00:20:25,865
If you don't

240
00:20:25,890 --> 00:20:27,558
I'll kill this girl!

241
00:20:28,917 --> 00:20:29,917
Supremo...

242
00:20:30,367 --> 00:20:31,911
Let's leave, Supremo.

243
00:20:32,620 --> 00:20:33,572
I'm not kidding!

244
00:20:33,597 --> 00:20:34,681
How could I forget?

245
00:20:34,830 --> 00:20:37,790
Other people's lives have no value to them.

246
00:20:37,791 --> 00:20:38,684
Zein!

247
00:20:38,709 --> 00:20:39,787
Even my life.

248
00:20:40,210 --> 00:20:41,544
Why would he help me?

249
00:20:41,545 --> 00:20:42,545
Let her go!

250
00:20:43,047 --> 00:20:44,889
I'm just his secretary.

251
00:20:45,507 --> 00:20:46,926
Let me go!

252
00:20:53,170 --> 00:20:55,194
Who are you going to kill again?

253
00:20:56,118 --> 00:20:56,952
Zein!

254
00:20:56,977 --> 00:20:58,180
Zein!

255
00:20:58,205 --> 00:20:59,707
Who'll die now?

256
00:21:06,594 --> 00:21:08,096
What's happening to you, Zein?

257
00:21:10,168 --> 00:21:11,381
Almost...

258
00:21:11,951 --> 00:21:13,452
he's still alive.

259
00:21:17,677 --> 00:21:18,845
Zein.

260
00:21:20,923 --> 00:21:21,923
You're bleeding.

261
00:21:27,416 --> 00:21:29,537
This won't kill me.

262
00:21:34,984 --> 00:21:36,444
Let me out of this hellhole!

263
00:21:48,779 --> 00:21:50,114
The wound is shallow.

264
00:21:52,032 --> 00:21:53,575
What happened to
you earlier, Zein?

265
00:21:56,221 --> 00:21:57,221
I don't know.

266
00:21:57,246 --> 00:21:58,914
It's like I was possessed.

267
00:22:00,124 --> 00:22:02,835
Even your eyes were
different earlier.

268
00:22:03,890 --> 00:22:07,643
It's like the eyes of a killer.

269
00:22:08,324 --> 00:22:09,492
That's too much.

270
00:22:10,050 --> 00:22:11,218
She didn't kill anyone,

271
00:22:12,175 --> 00:22:13,467
Jerome. Stop it.

272
00:22:14,437 --> 00:22:15,438
I know that

273
00:22:15,990 --> 00:22:17,117
but...

274
00:22:17,602 --> 00:22:19,270
she became different.

275
00:22:20,621 --> 00:22:22,957
I even hesitated if
I should help Matt

276
00:22:23,605 --> 00:22:26,525
but I was afraid that
you might stab me.

277
00:22:28,065 --> 00:22:29,959
Zein won't do that.

278
00:22:32,085 --> 00:22:33,885
But you were a different
person earlier, Zein.

279
00:22:34,705 --> 00:22:36,248
I felt your rage.

280
00:22:36,984 --> 00:22:38,384
It's like you turned
into a monster.

281
00:22:39,107 --> 00:22:40,107
Me?

282
00:22:40,661 --> 00:22:41,661
A monster?

283
00:22:44,887 --> 00:22:46,556
You're wasting your
time, nurse Cha.

284
00:22:47,275 --> 00:22:48,405
That's just a flesh wound.

285
00:22:52,124 --> 00:22:53,124
Who was that?

286
00:22:53,510 --> 00:22:54,595
That's Dr. Razon.

287
00:22:55,012 --> 00:22:56,537
There's a doctor here?

288
00:22:57,056 --> 00:22:59,683
He doesn't seem to care
about us students.

289
00:24:04,456 --> 00:24:05,456
What happened?

290
00:24:06,458 --> 00:24:07,167
Where have you been?

291
00:24:07,168 --> 00:24:08,377
I got stuck outside.

292
00:24:09,169 --> 00:24:12,155
I was hiding until
the chaos stopped.

293
00:24:25,920 --> 00:24:26,999
Where are they?

294
00:24:27,756 --> 00:24:28,756
Don't tell me...

295
00:24:29,544 --> 00:24:30,544
This can't be.

296
00:24:30,716 --> 00:24:31,836
I shouldn't think this way.

297
00:24:35,334 --> 00:24:36,964
But if they're not in their rooms

298
00:24:37,059 --> 00:24:38,936
that only means one thing.

299
00:24:48,029 --> 00:24:49,614
This has been going
on for a while.

300
00:24:52,663 --> 00:24:53,663
Van?

301
00:25:00,932 --> 00:25:03,184
They leave every night.

302
00:25:05,994 --> 00:25:06,911
What?

303
00:25:06,936 --> 00:25:08,478
We need to find them!

304
00:25:09,062 --> 00:25:10,062
Zein

305
00:25:10,227 --> 00:25:12,104
not tonight, please.

306
00:25:12,983 --> 00:25:13,983
Van

307
00:25:14,401 --> 00:25:15,819
what is happening?

308
00:25:17,224 --> 00:25:19,893
Have you known they were
sneaking out all this time?

309
00:25:20,174 --> 00:25:21,342
I'm scared, Zein.

310
00:25:24,161 --> 00:25:25,162
Of what?

311
00:25:28,874 --> 00:25:34,671
I've been waking up at night
recurringly with the boys gone.

312
00:25:36,673 --> 00:25:37,799
Sometimes Matt

313
00:25:39,051 --> 00:25:40,051
then Dave

314
00:25:40,719 --> 00:25:42,262
and Jerome.

315
00:25:43,430 --> 00:25:45,682
I don't know where
they're sneaking off to.

316
00:25:46,225 --> 00:25:48,602
But they keep leaving
during Bloody Night.

317
00:25:52,397 --> 00:25:54,358
I'll figure out where they keep going to.

318
00:25:54,858 --> 00:25:56,235
Zein, please.

319
00:25:58,028 --> 00:25:59,028
Van...

320
00:25:59,545 --> 00:26:01,714
We're the only ones here.

321
00:26:04,159 --> 00:26:05,369
Let's stick together.

322
00:26:06,036 --> 00:26:07,745
Just this night.

323
00:26:07,746 --> 00:26:08,746
Please.

324
00:26:09,706 --> 00:26:10,958
Please, Zein.

325
00:26:18,674 --> 00:26:20,884
Didn't we already talk about this, Van?

326
00:26:22,261 --> 00:26:24,763
This is only for emergencies.

327
00:26:25,500 --> 00:26:27,586
We need to survive Bloody Week

328
00:26:28,035 --> 00:26:29,786
if we want to leave this place.

329
00:26:30,519 --> 00:26:32,562
Our lives are in danger, Zein.

330
00:26:33,480 --> 00:26:35,732
If we don't help ourselves

331
00:26:35,983 --> 00:26:37,651
who will help us?

332
00:26:54,293 --> 00:26:55,961
Help!

333
00:26:56,253 --> 00:26:58,422
Help me!

334
00:26:59,006 --> 00:26:59,923
Jerome?

335
00:26:59,924 --> 00:27:02,049
Help me!

336
00:27:02,050 --> 00:27:04,343
Please!

337
00:27:04,344 --> 00:27:05,344
Jerome!

338
00:27:09,433 --> 00:27:10,767
Help me!

339
00:27:10,952 --> 00:27:15,289
♪ Happy birthday to you! ♪

340
00:27:15,314 --> 00:27:19,483
♪ Happy birthday to you! ♪

341
00:27:19,484 --> 00:27:21,777
♪ Happy birthday. ♪

342
00:27:21,778 --> 00:27:25,532
♪ Happy birthday. ♪

343
00:27:25,866 --> 00:27:31,204
♪ Happy birthday to you! ♪

344
00:27:32,914 --> 00:27:34,415
Oh my god, Jerome.

345
00:27:34,416 --> 00:27:36,250
You guys scared me there!

346
00:27:36,251 --> 00:27:38,377
Happy birthday, Ms. Secretary!

347
00:27:38,378 --> 00:27:39,754
Happy birthday!

348
00:27:39,755 --> 00:27:40,672
Thank you so much guys!

349
00:27:40,673 --> 00:27:43,258
I forgot my own birhtday.

350
00:27:43,564 --> 00:27:46,695
It's because you have too
much on your mind!

351
00:27:46,720 --> 00:27:49,306
Good thing we thought about you.

352
00:27:49,723 --> 00:27:50,615
Did we do a good job?

353
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:51,807
Super!

354
00:27:51,808 --> 00:27:53,018
Thank you so much guys.

355
00:27:53,435 --> 00:27:54,644
But you didn't have to.

356
00:27:55,354 --> 00:27:56,605
Of course, Zein.

357
00:27:56,980 --> 00:27:59,524
Go on, Matt. Aren't you
going to greet Zein?

358
00:28:00,233 --> 00:28:03,653
He's right, your saliva
will dry up.

359
00:28:04,529 --> 00:28:06,782
I'm doing it, guys.

360
00:28:07,532 --> 00:28:09,785
That's our boy.

361
00:28:18,689 --> 00:28:20,107
Happy birthday, Zein.

362
00:28:26,551 --> 00:28:27,886
That's our boy!

363
00:28:52,009 --> 00:28:53,261
Thank you, Matt.

364
00:28:58,236 --> 00:28:59,946
She's turning red!

365
00:29:00,470 --> 00:29:02,639
I think she's more than okay.

366
00:29:03,046 --> 00:29:05,382
Let's go, Zein. Blow the candle?

367
00:29:07,566 --> 00:29:08,566
Here she comes.

368
00:29:09,344 --> 00:29:10,846
Make a wish.

369
00:29:15,253 --> 00:29:17,254
Yey!

370
00:29:17,279 --> 00:29:19,365
Happy birthday!

371
00:29:20,230 --> 00:29:22,983
Let's eat!

372
00:29:23,608 --> 00:29:24,985
Let's go!

373
00:29:25,068 --> 00:29:27,446
And because it's your
birthday, sit in the middle.

374
00:29:27,904 --> 00:29:29,321
Our princess.

375
00:29:29,322 --> 00:29:30,824
Thank you, guys.

376
00:29:31,950 --> 00:29:33,118
Who cooked this?

377
00:29:33,994 --> 00:29:37,414
Of course, there's no one but Mia!

378
00:29:37,998 --> 00:29:39,249
Wow, Mia!

379
00:29:47,632 --> 00:29:48,632
Okay?

380
00:29:49,092 --> 00:29:50,092
Yeah.

381
00:29:57,601 --> 00:29:59,143
It says in the student records

382
00:29:59,144 --> 00:30:01,146
that the percentage of absentees are high.

383
00:30:01,480 --> 00:30:03,023
List it down. Okay?

384
00:30:03,106 --> 00:30:04,106
Prepare it.

385
00:30:04,858 --> 00:30:05,858
I'll take care of it.

386
00:30:06,818 --> 00:30:08,653
Check it properly since you volunteered.

387
00:30:08,945 --> 00:30:10,279
Make sure you won't make any mistakes

388
00:30:10,280 --> 00:30:12,073
or Supremo will reprimand you again.

389
00:30:12,741 --> 00:30:13,592
Fine.

390
00:30:13,617 --> 00:30:15,367
Since you guys can’t expect anything

391
00:30:15,368 --> 00:30:17,704
from your good for nothing secretary.

392
00:31:54,965 --> 00:31:55,965
Hey

393
00:31:58,513 --> 00:31:59,681
why are you so damn happy?

394
00:32:01,683 --> 00:32:03,268
That's none of your business.

395
00:32:04,482 --> 00:32:05,490
Watch your words.

396
00:32:10,108 --> 00:32:11,108
Onel!

397
00:32:12,830 --> 00:32:13,872
What's the occassion?

398
00:32:14,738 --> 00:32:19,022
I think it's better if you
ask Ms. Secretary, Supremo.

399
00:32:22,782 --> 00:32:24,701
What? I don't know anything.

400
00:32:40,639 --> 00:32:42,848
Okay, can somebody just tell me

401
00:32:42,849 --> 00:32:44,434
what we're supposed
to be celebrating?

402
00:32:52,672 --> 00:32:53,672
Nevermind.

403
00:32:53,906 --> 00:32:54,906
Just leave!

404
00:32:55,779 --> 00:32:56,779
All of you.

405
00:33:12,629 --> 00:33:14,047
Why are you so happy?

406
00:33:15,215 --> 00:33:16,591
Why are you smiling?

407
00:33:19,094 --> 00:33:20,303
Am I not allowed to?

408
00:33:22,356 --> 00:33:23,357
You know

409
00:33:23,973 --> 00:33:25,975
instead of wasting your time

410
00:33:26,630 --> 00:33:28,674
thinking about why I'm smiling

411
00:33:29,521 --> 00:33:31,815
you should focus on Bloody Week.

412
00:33:32,419 --> 00:33:34,755
Cause what's happening around us
should be taken seriously.

413
00:33:36,455 --> 00:33:37,455
Fine.

414
00:33:38,371 --> 00:33:39,621
Just leave me alone.

415
00:33:39,646 --> 00:33:40,689
Gladly.

416
00:33:42,053 --> 00:33:43,218
I said leave.

417
00:33:43,243 --> 00:33:44,785
Okay, I'm leaving.

418
00:33:44,967 --> 00:33:46,286
So impatient.

419
00:33:46,395 --> 00:33:47,313
I'm leaving.

420
00:33:47,338 --> 00:33:48,338
Bye!

421
00:34:00,361 --> 00:34:02,112
Why does he care if I'm smiling?

422
00:34:02,277 --> 00:34:04,330
He should mind his own business.

423
00:34:04,355 --> 00:34:05,565
Just like yesterday

424
00:34:05,807 --> 00:34:09,639
when someone tried to kill
me and he didn't do anything.

425
00:34:29,750 --> 00:34:30,834
He was right.

426
00:34:33,485 --> 00:34:34,861
You're weird.

427
00:34:39,860 --> 00:34:42,006
Um... Zein right?

428
00:34:47,116 --> 00:34:48,659
You amaze me.

429
00:34:51,497 --> 00:34:53,280
You're really one of a kind.

430
00:34:56,516 --> 00:34:59,269
I saw how you defended yourself yesterday.

431
00:35:03,628 --> 00:35:05,254
I can only tell you one thing

432
00:35:07,470 --> 00:35:09,138
he believes in you.

433
00:35:11,104 --> 00:35:13,815
Even if he wanted to help you

434
00:35:15,196 --> 00:35:17,198
he restrained himself from doing it.

435
00:35:21,998 --> 00:35:23,541
I had my doubts but.

436
00:35:24,776 --> 00:35:26,111
I was wrong.

437
00:35:31,335 --> 00:35:41,335
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

438
00:35:33,360 --> 00:35:34,528
I'm sorry

439
00:35:34,870 --> 00:35:36,664
I've been blabbering.

440
00:35:36,744 --> 00:35:37,744
Okay,

441
00:35:38,008 --> 00:35:39,259
I'll go ahead.

442
00:35:42,612 --> 00:35:44,781
What is she talking about?

443
00:35:45,098 --> 00:35:47,267
Do I have the wrong impression about Ace?

444
00:35:47,916 --> 00:35:50,594
Why are people acting so weird today?

445
00:36:09,790 --> 00:36:12,417
It could've been perfect.

446
00:36:12,637 --> 00:36:16,905
If only someone added sugar in the cake.

447
00:36:16,930 --> 00:36:17,930
True.

448
00:36:18,075 --> 00:36:21,377
It was already tastleless,
but it collapsed too!

449
00:36:21,401 --> 00:36:22,794
What a waste.

450
00:36:22,964 --> 00:36:26,271
I know, it's my fault.

451
00:36:26,573 --> 00:36:28,323
I got tensed and distracted by the smoke

452
00:36:28,324 --> 00:36:30,409
that's why I forgot to add in sugar.

453
00:36:30,410 --> 00:36:32,202
I'm sorry, Zein. I'm sorry.

454
00:36:32,242 --> 00:36:34,957
At least we decorated it well.

455
00:36:34,982 --> 00:36:36,415
It looked like an actual birthday cake.

456
00:36:36,416 --> 00:36:37,250
He's right.

457
00:36:37,250 --> 00:36:38,250
Right, Matt?

458
00:36:38,467 --> 00:36:40,478
And it's the thought that counts.

459
00:36:40,503 --> 00:36:41,753
You liked it, didn't you, Zein?

460
00:36:41,754 --> 00:36:42,714
Of course.

461
00:36:42,714 --> 00:36:43,800
I enjoyed it.

462
00:36:43,825 --> 00:36:44,798
Thank you, guys.

463
00:36:44,799 --> 00:36:47,176
I couldn't ask for more.

464
00:36:49,663 --> 00:36:51,331
You guys look like you're having fun.

465
00:36:52,510 --> 00:36:54,220
Here he is again.

466
00:36:56,777 --> 00:36:58,654
But I need my secretary.

467
00:37:01,996 --> 00:37:04,957
Can't you function without your secretary?

468
00:37:07,422 --> 00:37:09,549
So I'm still his secretary, huh?

469
00:37:09,660 --> 00:37:12,122
I thought I was already replaced.

470
00:37:12,561 --> 00:37:13,561
Sorry guys,

471
00:37:14,337 --> 00:37:15,346
duty calls.

472
00:37:15,371 --> 00:37:16,371
You can go ahead.

473
00:37:16,645 --> 00:37:19,190
Let's see each other at the dorm later.

474
00:37:20,084 --> 00:37:21,060
Okay?

475
00:37:21,085 --> 00:37:22,503
Um, okay.

476
00:37:33,355 --> 00:37:34,690
What do you need?

477
00:37:36,458 --> 00:37:38,752
You really won't tell me about it?

478
00:37:42,070 --> 00:37:43,780
Did I really have to look into it?

479
00:37:44,953 --> 00:37:46,663
Do you enjoy giving me a hard time?

480
00:37:51,271 --> 00:37:53,490
I knew there was
something about your smile.

481
00:37:55,258 --> 00:37:56,843
You made my head hurt from thinking.

482
00:37:57,773 --> 00:37:58,774
Huh?

483
00:38:08,028 --> 00:38:09,196
Happy birthday...

484
00:38:09,860 --> 00:38:10,860
Zein.

485
00:38:11,511 --> 00:38:14,781
I always thought Ace ignored my existance.

486
00:38:14,806 --> 00:38:16,057
That he didn't care.

487
00:38:16,641 --> 00:38:18,226
But with three words,

488
00:38:20,097 --> 00:38:23,021
he made me feel seen.

489
00:38:25,767 --> 00:38:28,978
And for whatever reason, I appreciate it.

490
00:38:31,990 --> 00:38:33,658
Good morning, students.

491
00:38:37,214 --> 00:38:38,381
What is this again?

492
00:38:39,440 --> 00:38:41,818
Do you find Bloody Week a little boring?

493
00:38:42,265 --> 00:38:43,558
Then let's play a game.

494
00:38:44,308 --> 00:38:46,466
To make Bloody Week more exciting!

495
00:38:47,068 --> 00:38:50,196
Look inside your lockers.

496
00:38:52,760 --> 00:38:56,300
On the paper are names you have to kill

497
00:38:56,325 --> 00:38:58,077
before the time runs out.

498
00:39:03,359 --> 00:39:05,111
If you didn't get a name.

499
00:39:09,741 --> 00:39:11,784
You are chosen to die.

500
00:39:26,287 --> 00:39:27,872
Did you know about this?

501
00:39:28,358 --> 00:39:29,358
No.

502
00:40:32,877 --> 00:40:34,170
Where are we going?

503
00:40:34,195 --> 00:40:35,140
Check your locker.

504
00:40:35,165 --> 00:40:36,540
Supremo's here. Let's go!

505
00:40:39,002 --> 00:40:40,002
Open it.

506
00:40:40,957 --> 00:40:42,208
Do I have to?

507
00:40:44,053 --> 00:40:45,804
Do I have to do this?

508
00:40:46,501 --> 00:40:48,295
Is this really happening?

509
00:40:49,426 --> 00:40:50,803
You can check it.

510
00:40:54,460 --> 00:40:55,919
I'll be here with you, okay?

511
00:40:56,701 --> 00:40:58,161
I'll stay with you.

512
00:40:59,303 --> 00:41:00,238
Hey...

513
00:41:00,568 --> 00:41:02,153
Hey.

514
00:41:02,879 --> 00:41:04,006
Calm down.

515
00:41:04,362 --> 00:41:05,488
Calm down, breathe.

516
00:41:06,156 --> 00:41:07,449
Calm down, okay?

517
00:41:08,421 --> 00:41:11,800
What if I pick one of my friends?

518
00:41:12,652 --> 00:41:13,945
Or your name?

519
00:41:15,763 --> 00:41:17,630
Don't look too far, okay?

520
00:41:17,889 --> 00:41:18,973
Let's check it first

521
00:41:19,393 --> 00:41:20,519
then we'll see from there.

522
00:41:21,064 --> 00:41:22,149
Okay?

523
00:42:07,788 --> 00:42:08,788
For you.

524
00:42:10,783 --> 00:42:11,783
What is it?

525
00:42:13,296 --> 00:42:14,327
A gift.

526
00:42:15,097 --> 00:42:16,390
For Bloody Night.

527
00:42:33,388 --> 00:42:34,680
There's nothing written here.

528
00:42:37,161 --> 00:42:38,245
Nothing.

529
00:43:15,314 --> 00:43:19,401
It will last one whole week!

530
00:43:19,700 --> 00:43:23,899
And we will call it Bloody Week.

531
00:43:23,924 --> 00:43:28,387
Where killing is legal for one whole week.

532
00:43:33,833 --> 00:43:35,309
I'm tired of you!

533
00:43:35,334 --> 00:43:36,811
I'm always you're target!

534
00:43:36,836 --> 00:43:38,543
I'm done with you embarassing me.

535
00:43:55,229 --> 00:43:56,869
- Be quiet. Don't come near us.
- Help me!

536
00:43:57,456 --> 00:43:59,166
Let me out of this hellhole!

537
00:43:59,519 --> 00:44:01,688
If you get targeted by the gangs

538
00:44:04,029 --> 00:44:05,823
you will never find peace again.

539
00:44:07,217 --> 00:44:08,217
No!

540
00:45:52,740 --> 00:45:55,492
I tried to ignore the
recurring disappearance

541
00:45:55,516 --> 00:45:59,145
of my friends during Bloody Night.

542
00:46:00,137 --> 00:46:02,139
But I can't turn a blind eye anymore.

543
00:46:02,773 --> 00:46:06,777
I need to know what's
happening with my friends.

544
00:46:51,363 --> 00:46:52,363
Hoy!

545
00:46:53,355 --> 00:46:54,300
Hoy!

546
00:46:54,450 --> 00:46:55,450
Did you hear that?

547
00:46:55,576 --> 00:46:56,656
Something moved back there.

548
00:46:57,286 --> 00:46:58,621
That's just the cat.

549
00:46:58,662 --> 00:46:59,538
Is he upstairs?

550
00:46:59,539 --> 00:47:01,803
Can we really trust him?

551
00:47:02,666 --> 00:47:03,976
He's instantly the co-leader?

552
00:47:04,001 --> 00:47:05,169
That doesn't make sense.

553
00:47:05,983 --> 00:47:07,401
What else can we do?

554
00:47:07,677 --> 00:47:08,677
Boss likes him.

555
00:47:08,920 --> 00:47:10,900
And let's give him a chance.

556
00:47:11,206 --> 00:47:12,999
Boss sees something in him.

557
00:47:13,653 --> 00:47:14,653
I hope he's right...

558
00:47:14,678 --> 00:47:16,388
This gang war has been tiring

559
00:47:16,680 --> 00:47:19,725
we always have to be one
step ahead of the DGW.

560
00:47:22,269 --> 00:47:23,269
Let's go.

561
00:47:23,513 --> 00:47:24,513
Let’s go.

562
00:47:25,981 --> 00:47:28,389
Let's hurry before Boss gets mad.

563
00:48:28,252 --> 00:48:30,087
I want you to see everything.

564
00:48:42,266 --> 00:48:43,601
Who is Van talking to?

565
00:48:44,351 --> 00:48:45,394
That's Liam.

566
00:48:48,689 --> 00:48:50,316
Who was written in your paper?

567
00:48:54,168 --> 00:48:55,210
Anonymous.

568
00:48:56,858 --> 00:48:59,100
There are things we should keep hidden.

569
00:49:02,995 --> 00:49:04,163
You're drunk.

570
00:49:07,439 --> 00:49:10,131
So what if I'm drunk?

571
00:49:12,152 --> 00:49:13,778
Even if I'm drunk.

572
00:49:14,684 --> 00:49:16,268
I know

573
00:49:16,767 --> 00:49:18,560
that you're still beautiful.

574
00:49:21,407 --> 00:49:25,911
You promised that when you find the
man you'll love for the rest of your life

575
00:49:26,827 --> 00:49:28,621
you'll love him forever.

576
00:49:28,646 --> 00:49:29,854
The wound is deep!

577
00:49:29,855 --> 00:49:30,522
Doc!

578
00:49:30,522 --> 00:49:31,106
Please hurry!

579
00:49:31,107 --> 00:49:32,366
Open the door!

580
00:49:32,391 --> 00:49:34,393
We're sorry but the clinic is closed today.

581
00:49:36,779 --> 00:49:38,113
Ms. Shion!
